	<p>@Shiv: remember, the author(s) of the website you're downloading has copyright over the <em>design</em>, including whatever code or markup powers it.  Copyright does NOT just cover content!
</p>
<p>So changing all the content but keeping the exact same layout and code may, in some cases, be an infringement that leads to somebody getting angry and asking you to remove your all-too-similar website.
</p>
<p>Of course, if the design is very common, this probably doesn't apply, or if the site design is open-sourced, e.g. Wordpress.
</p>
