	</div>
	<p>E is right, if your site is dynamic, then you will get files such as something.php?this=that . This won't work unless your mirror server serves php files as HTML ones.
</p>
<p>So in order to mirror a dynamic website it is necessary to move databases. I am not sure if wget is suitable for this purpose since there is different access to databases than to public folders with website's content.
</p>
